interactions.flavorLineOne: For a split second, it seemed like Louis was staring at you. Hawthorne didn't seem to notice. She accepts the gift on his behalf.

"The people of the City are excited about the Guardian Games," Hawthorne says as you walk up. "We don't usually get to see you Guardians in action.

"The way you all came together during the Red War… the way you risked your lives even when you couldn't be sure you'd come back." She nods. "It meant a lot. And I know you're still protecting the City every day. So…" She smiles at you. "Let's celebrate."
Hawthorne is impressed by your dedication to bringing more Guardians into the fold, and she offers a reward in return.

"The people of the City use this holiday to bring a little levity to our grim reality," Hawthorne says. "We're scared, but we're laughing."

She pauses and gives you a meaningful look. "I think Guardians can probably relate."
Hawthorne may not say it out loud, but she's proud of how you and your friend never quit. She gives you a reward for your persistence.

"It's a lonely system, Guardian. Being in a clan makes it a little bit easier." —Hawthorne

headerDisplayProperties.description: Speak to Hawthorne to collect your reward.
headerDisplayProperties.name: Clan Rewards

interactions.flavorLineOne: Both Louis and his lifelong friend appreciate the thoughtful gift you've brought them. Louis seems calmer already.

"Hey… You put together a fireteam, stepped into the belly of the beast, and lived to tell the tale. Few can say the same. I'm impressed, Guardian."

Continue to rally your fireteam and challenge yourselves to complete raid activities to earn even more XP and more powerful rewards!

Represent your clan well, Guardian.

This banner will grow in strength as your clan demonstrates its power.

We have witnessed the miraculous: the Traveler has reawakened… and Hawthorne has returned to the City. Zavala convinced her to continue her role as guide for both new and old Guardians. She found her place in this new community, bridging the gap between humanity and the Guardians who protect them. 

Visit Hawthorne for all of your clan-related activities.
Hawthorne doesn't trust the Drifter, but she supports you and your friend working together to push back the enemies of humanity.
Hawthorne congratulates you and your friend on reaching a significant milestone, and she offers a reward to help celebrate.

Hawthorne prefers the solitary life, choosing to live beyond the Wall. Despite this, she took charge of this camp to help the refugees of the City survive in unfamiliar and dangerous lands. She wants to help you out and offers you a ship for your journey. 

Follow your vision to the Shard of the Traveler by completing mission SPARK in the EDZ.

We have a new plan. The Vanguard will lead a host of Lightless Guardians on a counteroffensive against the occupied City, hoping to free the Traveler. Meanwhile, you must disable the Almighty's sun-killing superweapon before it can destroy the entire solar system. To approach the Almighty undetected, steal the personal ship of Thumos the Unbroken, one of Ghaul's chosen Blood Guard. 

Bring the fight back to the Red Legion by completing mission "Payback" in the EDZ.
Hawthorne doesn't trust the Drifter, but she supports you and your friend working together to push back the enemies of humanity.

Your vision from the Traveler was true and it led you back to the Light. The camp is even safer now that you have reconnected to your power. But there are still a lot of people out there in the wild who need refuge. Help get them to the Farm. 

Go meet Hawthorne's friend Devrim by selecting the landing zone TROSTLAND in the EDZ.
Hawthorne congratulates you and your friend on reaching a significant milestone, and she offers a reward to help celebrate.

"Feeling confident, Guardian? You'll learn fast that survival isn't just about skill. Having friends who'll cover your blind spots in pinch is crucial if you're gonna hunt big game."

Hawthorne offers challenges, consumables, XP, and rewards for completing raid activities.

Gather your fireteam and take on the "Leviathan" raid to prove you can work as a team, and earn powerful rewards!
Hawthorne recognizes your shared commitment with another Guardian and is eager to challenge the two of you to prove that connection.

interactions.flavorLineOne: Hawthorne has worked with plenty of shady characters in the past, so she's more understanding of your collaboration with the Drifter than most. She offers you a reward for your clan's Gambit performance.
"Not sure what this 'Nine' nonsense is all about, but apparently your clan did some good stuff in their Trials. These 'spoils' were left for you." —Hawthorne

headerDisplayProperties.name: Clan Engram: Trials of the Nine

interactions.flavorLineOne:
The strongest clan is one that works together. 

When you prove your strength, come back, and we'll have a little something for you.
"Looks like your clan's been impressing Shaxx and company. I bet I could hold my own in the Crucible. Whaddaya think?" —Hawthorne
"Whatever your clan's been doing out there, Zavala's pretty impressed." —Hawthorne
"Your clan's been busy, taking care of threats to the system that would have sent other clans running. The City's noticed, and… well, we'd like you to have this." —Hawthorne
